## Repository Rules

```text
app/api/routes/      HTTP contracts only
app/services/        business logic and orchestration
app/repositories/    persistence access only
app/models/          pydantic schemas and domain data shapes
app/core/            settings, app bootstrap, auth wiring
app/workers/         async jobs and out-of-band processing
tests/integration/   API + persistence integration coverage
```

## Non-Negotiable Boundaries

1. Route handlers may validate request shape and call services. They must not hold business logic.
2. Services own workflow logic, permission checks, and orchestration.
3. Repositories are the only layer allowed to talk to the database.
4. Long-running work leaves the request path and goes into `app/workers/`.
5. Configuration is loaded centrally from `app/core/settings.py`.

## FastAPI Conventions

- Prefer `APIRouter` per resource.
- Prefer typed dependencies over ad-hoc globals.
- Keep request models, response models, and domain entities separate when they diverge.
- Return consistent error envelopes and do not leak stack traces.
{% if api_docs %}
- Keep OpenAPI output trustworthy; schema drift is a bug.
{% endif %}

## Authentication Rules

{% if auth_strategy == "none" %}
- No auth is configured. Do not add ad-hoc auth middleware without documenting the decision first.
{% elif auth_strategy == "jwt" %}
- JWT verification belongs in a shared dependency or security helper, not inside route functions.
- Keep authorization checks in services after identity has been resolved.
{% elif auth_strategy == "oauth2" %}
- OAuth2 client, scopes, and callback handling belong in infrastructure code.
- Services should work with resolved principals, not provider-specific token payloads.
{% else %}
- API key verification belongs in shared dependencies.
- Store only hashed keys; never log raw key values.
{% endif %}

## Testing Rules

{% if test_strategy == "pytest-only" %}
- Keep service logic heavily unit-tested with pytest.
- Add a small number of HTTP smoke integration tests.
{% elif test_strategy == "pytest-and-integration" %}
- Every business-critical service branch gets unit tests.
- Every externally visible resource gets integration coverage for happy path and authorization failures.
{% else %}
- Treat unit, integration, and workflow-level verification as separate concerns.
- Do not merge broad workflow changes without cross-layer verification.
{% endif %}

## Implementation Heuristics

- Build one resource vertically first: schema -> repository -> service -> route -> test.
- Prefer explicit types and small modules over shared utility dumping grounds.
- Document structural exceptions in `docs/adrs/`.
